w1.notes:
*Both casts count as ability activations for the purposes of on-cast effects such as {{tip|Spellblade}} and stacking {{ai|Force Pulse|Kassadin}}.
* Mimicked abilities count as separate casts when they both hit the same target (e.g. for the purposes of {{ri|Electrocute}}, {{ri|Phase Rush}}, {{ii|Eclipse}}, etc).
* The {{tip|energy}} refund is not granted if the mimicked ability is blocked by a {{tip|spell shield}}.
* ''Living Shadow'' cannot be recast while {{tip|ground|grounded}} or {{tip|root|rooted}}.
* [[File:Zed's Shadow.png|20px|border]] ''Shadows'' grant {{tip|sight}} of their surroundings (700 radius) and they are {{tip|untargetable}}.
* If ''Living Shadow'' is recast during {{ai|Q|Zed}}, '''Zed''' will instantly release the shuriken from his original position while still remaining in cast time, and the [[File:Zed's Shadow.png|20px|border]] ''Shadow'' will release the shuriken based on '''Zed's''' remaining cast time.{{bug|1}}
* The [[File:Zed's Shadow.png|20px|border]] ''Shadow'' will cast {{ai|E|Zed}} independently of being in {{ais|Q|Zed}} cast time or not.{{bug|2}}
* '''Zed''' will swap places with the [[File:Zed's Shadow.png|20px|border]] ''Shadow'' by all means if he buffers ''Living Shadow's'' recast during its dash.{{bug|2}}
** ''Living Shadow'' cannot be recast while '''Zed''' is marking his target with {{ai|R|Zed}}, but may still be recast if it was buffered.{{bug|1}}
* If '''Zed''' casts ''Living Shadow'' while a non-''{{ai|Death Mark 2|Zed|Death Mark}} Shadow'' is already present, the previous ''Shadow'' will instantly disappear.
* [[File:Zed's Shadow.png|20px|border]] ''Shadows'' will not disappear when '''Zed''' dies.{{bug}}
* '''Zed''' always has an ''arrow'' next to him pointing in the direction of his [[File:Zed's Shadow.png|20px|border]] ''Shadows''. It has three different colors, each one symbolizes important information about the specific ''Shadow.'' They are only visible to '''Zed'''.
